All GRB triggering is automated using the TRACE-T web application, which was designed and written with the support of the Astronomy Data and Compute Services (ADACS) based in Australia (PI Gemma Anderson). TRACE-T receives and parses astronomical transient alerts broadcast via the NASA Kafka General Coordinates Network (GCN), which go through a user-definited decision logic that results in the automatic triggering of observations with the Australia Telescope Compact Array (ATCA). Details on an early implementation of the code can be found in Anderson et al. (2021). If you are interested in using TRACE-T to trigger your own observations with ATCA (or the Murchison Widefield Array), please contact gemma.anderson@curtin.edu.au.
